{
  "description": "Conv2d (C_in=96, C_out=96, H=W=32, k=3x3, pad=1, stride=1, int8). Tiled im2col-GEMM-SiLU pipeline, Tile_M=32 (32 output pixels/tile), K=864=96*3*3, N=96. 4 representative tiles (of 32 total). Steady-state/no-halo abstraction: each tile source is modeled as 32 gathered receptive fields, so PATCH_A/PATCH_B each hold 32x864B = 27648B. Memory: WEIGHT_BUF(82944B)+IM2COL_A+IM2COL_B(2x27648B)+PATCH_A+PATCH_B(2x27648B)+OUTPUT_C(3072B)=192KiB. HW: 8 cores, 1 ext-narrow (idle), 3 wide HWPEs: DMA(id0)/GEMM(id1)/DataMover(id2). DMA: weight preload + double-buffered patch prefetch + output drain. DataMover: patch-pack/im2col traffic model (PATCH -> IM2COL, same byte volume). GEMM: IM2COL x WEIGHT -> OUTPUT_C. Cores: in-place SiLU activation with true read-modify-write traffic (8 cores partition OUTPUT_C into 384B chunks). Double-buffering: PATCH_A/IM2COL_A for even tiles, PATCH_B/IM2COL_B for odd tiles. Memory map (base: WEIGHT=0x00000, IM2COL_A=0x14400, IM2COL_B=0x1B000, PATCH_A=0x21C00, PATCH_B=0x28800, OUTPUT_C=0x2F400).",
